## Flow A — Browse & Enquire (Primary)

1

**Homepage** → Hero banner or nav click

2

**Collection page** (e.g., Floor Tiles) → filter by finish/brand/size → browse grid

3

**Product Detail Page** → view photos, check availability, read description

4

Click **"Enquire Now"** → Enquiry modal pre-filled with product → submit name/phone/message

5

**Owner notified** in real-time (push notification in dashboard \+ email/WhatsApp)

6

Customer receives **confirmation message** ("We'll contact you within 2 hours")

Drop-off risk at Step 4: if modal is too long → keep form to 3 fields max (Name, Phone, Message optional)

## Flow B — Shop by Area

1

Homepage → "Shop By Area" section → click **"Bathroom"** tile

2

Bathroom curated collection → all relevant tiles \+ fittings for bathroom space

3

Select product → PDP → Enquire Now → same as Flow A step 4–6

## Flow C — AR Visualization

1

PDP → click **"View in My Space"** (AR tab or AR button)

2

Permission prompt: "Allow camera access to visualize this tile in your room" → Allow

3

Camera feed opens → product overlaid → customer drags/scales to position on floor/wall

4

Screenshot → share or save → return to PDP

5

After AR: "Like what you see? Enquire Now →" contextual CTA shown

Conversion trigger: show enquiry CTA immediately after AR session ends

## Flow D — AI Room Makeover

1

Homepage → "Try AI Makeover →" CTA or nav → **/ai-makeover**

2

Step 1: Upload room photo (bathroom / kitchen / living room)

3

Step 2: Select preferences — style (Modern/Traditional/Luxe/Minimal/Industrial) \+ dominant colour

4

Step 3: Gemini API generates redesigned room → shows before/after slider

5

Below generated image: **"Products Used in This Design"** → catalog of 3–5 suggested products each with "Enquire Now"

6

Customer enquires on suggested products → Flow A step 4–6

## Flow E — Store Visit Appointment

1

Nav "Book Visit" CTA or PDP "Book Store Visit" button → **/book-visit**

2

Select category(s) of interest → choose date → choose time slot → enter name/phone

3

Submit → confirmation screen with store address \+ "Add to Calendar"

4

Owner receives notification in dashboard → confirms/reschedules

5

Customer receives WhatsApp/SMS confirmation with store address and date/time

## Flow F — Video Call Enquiry

1

PDP → "Request Video Call" button → modal

2

Customer fills: name, phone, preferred date/time, notes, platform preference (Google Meet / WhatsApp Video)

3

Owner notified → confirms time → video link sent via WhatsApp/email

4

Video call happens → post-call: "Did your query get resolved?" feedback form with option to submit formal enquiry

## Flow G — AI Chatbot Assistance

1

Customer on any page → clicks **Chatbot FAB** (bottom-right)

2

Chatbot opens: "Hi\! I'm here to help you find the perfect tiles and hardware. What are you looking for?"

3

Customer describes need (e.g., "anti-skid floor tiles for bathroom") → Gemini responds with category suggestions \+ product links

4

If complex query: chatbot says "Let me connect you with our team" → opens WhatsApp with conversation context

5

Lead captured: chatbot interaction logged as enquiry in owner dashboard

## Flow H — Similar Products Catalog Discovery

1

Customer on PDP → scrolls down to "More in Floor Tiles" section → sees 50+ compact product cards

2

Customer spots a different variant (different size/finish/brand) → clicks "Enquire for This" micro-button directly on compact card

3

Mini enquiry modal (smaller, pre-filled) → Name \+ Phone → Submit

4

Owner notified with specific product reference

## Flow I — Owner Enquiry Management

1

Owner logs in → Dashboard shows real-time enquiry feed (Supabase Realtime)

2

New enquiry notification → sound \+ badge → click to expand enquiry details

3

Owner sees: customer name, phone, product reference, message, enquiry channel, timestamp

4

Actions: Mark responded | Call customer | Open WhatsApp | Archive

5

Enquiry moves from "New" → "In Progress" → "Resolved"

